ep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2b70a48-4cbf-46dd-b88c-0c4d88f4bb94_900x506.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2b70a48-4cbf-46dd-b88c-0c4d88f4bb94_900x506.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2b70a48-4cbf-46dd-b88c-0c4d88f4bb94_900x506.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2b70a48-4cbf-46dd-b88c-0c4d88f4bb94_900x506.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：世界大型企业联合会<a href="https://twitter.com/paulkrugman/status/1677747031987634176">，Paul Krugman</a>提供</figcaption></figure></div><h4><a href="https://twitter.com/paulkrugman/status/1677747031987634176">3.“电动汽车放缓”的说法是假的</a></h4><p>许多人声称向电动汽车的转变正在停滞，至少在美国是这样。例如，<a href="https://www.economist.com/business/2023/11/27/is-americas-ev-revolution-stalling">这是一周前的《经济学人》</a> 、<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/11/01/why-dealers-say-ev-sales-have-slowed.html">这是一个月前的 CNBC</a> 、<a href="https://money.com/why-americans-not-buying-electric-cars/">这是 Money.com</a>等等。</p><p>但这些文章似乎都没有提供令人信服的证据来支持该论文！ 《经济学人》援引皮尤民意调查显示，人们对电动汽车的兴趣下降，而不是实际销量下降，然后迅速转向将美国与中国和欧洲（电动汽车的采用速度非常快）进行比较。 <a href="https://www.economist.com/cdn-cgi/image/width=384,quality=80,format=auto/content-assets/images/20231202_WBC544.png">他们的图表</a>显示美国电动汽车销量仍在增长！ CNBC 引用了经销商需要多长时间才能出售电动汽车库存的数据，但考虑到销量的增加，这只是经销商过于乐观并订购了太多的迹象。 Money.com 的文章将电动汽车销量与预期进行比较，而不是与上一年的实际销量进行比较。</p><p>当你查看实际数据时，很明显，到目前为止实际上并没有放缓。美国人在 2023 年购买的电动汽车比 2022 年全年多了 20 万辆： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg" width="900" height="565" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:565,&quot;width&quot;:900,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:93836,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F72bb6ce6-3dec-4244-a0c3-cd15e025a7c5_900x565.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：科里·坎托</figcaption></figure></div><p></p><p>抱歉，仅仅因为电动汽车销量低于预期，或低于欧洲和中国，并不意味着电动汽车转型已经“停滞”。这只是意味着我们需要<em>进一步</em>加速转型。是的，充电站的缺乏以及一些美国人尚未相信电动汽车是未来这一事实值得担心。但有关电动汽车革命“停滞”的说法似乎是一种虚假趋势。</p><h4> 4.美国孩子受过良好教育，除了数学</h4><p>我<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/refusing-to-teach-kids-math-will">经常抱怨</a>美国数学教育质量差。数学焦虑在我们的文化中普遍存在，而且我们往往<a href="https://twitter.com/cremieuxrecueil/status/1730646739407851962">低估了这个学科</a>。但话虽如此，我们教育系统的整体表现实际上并没有那么糟糕。 <a href="https://www.axios.com/2023/12/05/us-students-pisa-global-assessment">PISA 结果已经出炉</a>，虽然美国的表现比以前更差——部分原因是大流行造成的学习损失——但我们仍然领先于中位数。</p><p>特别是，如果你按种族细分美国 PISA 成绩，你会发现，虽然我们的数学教育体系高度<em>不平等</em>，但并不像你想象的那么糟糕。美国黑人孩子<a href="https://twitter.com/cremieuxrecueil/status/1732087511327908128">的表现优于</a>罗马尼亚、希腊和保加利亚的孩子，而西班牙裔美国孩子的表现则优于斯洛伐克、冰岛和塞尔维亚的孩子： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6b0c7b95-ad1e-4649-b7bd-f59c5c912534_1228x983.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/h