tatus/1730756792290836950">反驳</a>说，由于通货膨胀已经下降——而且从未像 20 世纪 70 年代那么严重——对经济的愤怒只是“情绪”。</p><p>基本上，拜登的支持者是对的。美国经济现在确实非常好。<a href="https://twitter.com/jasonfurman/status/1730229041049874546">通货膨胀看起来已经被击败</a>，每个人都有工作，收入和财富都在增加，等等。但另一方面，我无法命令人们停止对 2021-22 年购买力下降的通货膨胀感到愤怒。人们关心他们关心的事情。</p><p>但与此同时，我认为有关经济的负面叙述可能会在普通民众中流行，并扭曲人们对实际情况的理解。例如，英国《金融时报》的约翰·伯恩-默多克<a href="https://t.co/FKpRNQkBVf">最近发现</a>，其他国家的消费者信心与实际经济指标密切相关，但自 2020 年以来在美国却出现了分化： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc5a18c0e-1cfb-4408-a4b0-f2986a2ad945_656x1200.jpeg" width="538" height="984.1463414